@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Product Care";
}

<div class="card mb-4">
    <div class="card-body">
        <h1 class="display-4 mb-4 text-center">Opal Care Guide</h1>
        <p class="lead text-center mb-5">Learn how to properly care for your precious opal jewelry</p>
        
        <div class="row mb-5">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <h3 class="mb-4">Understanding Opals</h3>
                <p>Opals are unique gemstones composed of silica spheres and water. They typically contain 5-10% water, which gives them their distinctive play of color but also makes them more delicate than many other gemstones.</p>
                <p>With proper care, your opal jewelry can be enjoyed for generations. This guide will help you understand how to maintain the beauty and integrity of your opal pieces.</p>
                
                <div class="alert alert-info mt-4">
                    <h5><i class="fas fa-info-circle me-2"></i> Opal Composition</h5>
                    <p class="mb-0">Opals are rated 5.5-6.5 on the Mohs hardness scale, making them softer than many gemstones like diamonds (10), sapphires (9), and even quartz (7).</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <div class="card h-100 bg-light">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="mb-3 text-center">Types of Opals</h4>
                        <div class="table-responsive">
                            <table class="table">
                                <thead class="table-primary">
                                    <tr>
                                        <th>Type</th>
                                        <th>Characteristics</th>
                                        <th>Special Care</th>
                                    </tr>
                                </thead>
                                <tbody>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Solid Opals</td>
                                        <td>Natural, solid pieces of opal</td>
                                        <td>Most susceptible to drying out</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Doublets</td>
                                        <td>Thin opal layer on backing material</td>
                                        <td>Avoid prolonged water exposure</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Triplets</td>
                                        <td>Opal layer with backing and clear cap</td>
                                        <td>Most durable, but avoid harsh chemicals</td>
                                    </tr>
                                </tbody>
                            </table>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="row mb-5">
            <div class="col-12">
                <h3 class="mb-4 text-center">Essential Care Guidelines</h3>
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
                        <div class="card h-100 care-card">
                            <div class="card-body text-center">
                                <div class="care-icon mb-3">
                                    <i class="fas fa-tint-slash fa-3x text-primary"></i>
                                </div>
                                <h4>Avoid Dehydration</h4>
                                <p>Opals contain water, and prolonged exposure to heat or dry conditions can cause them to dehydrate and potentially crack. Store your opals away from heat sources and consider occasional gentle moisturizing.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
                        <div class="card h-100 care-card">
                            <div class="card-body text-center">
                                <div class="care-icon mb-3">
                                    <i class="fas fa-hand-sparkles fa-3x text-primary"></i>
                                </div>
                                <h4>Gentle Cleaning</h4>
                                <p>Clean your opal jewelry with a soft, damp cloth. For more thorough cleaning, use mild soap and lukewarm water. Gently pat dry with a soft cloth and allow to air dry completely before storing.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="col-md-4 mb-4">
                        <div class="card h-100 care-card">
                            <div class="card-body text-center">
                                <div class="care-icon mb-3">
                                    <i class="fas fa-box-open fa-3x text-primary"></i>
                                </div>
                                <h4>Proper Storage</h4>
                                <p>Store opals separately from other jewelry to prevent scratches. Keep them in a soft pouch or lined jewelry box. For long-term storage, consider keeping a small damp cloth in the container to maintain humidity.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="row mb-5">
            <div class="col-12">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header bg-danger text-white">
                        <h3 class="mb-0">What to Avoid</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-md-6">
                                <ul class="avoid-list">
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>Extreme Temperatures</strong>
                                        <p>Sudden temperature changes can cause opals to crack. Remove opal jewelry before hot showers, saunas, or swimming in cold water.</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>Harsh Chemicals</strong>
                                        <p>Remove opal jewelry before using household cleaners, perfumes, hairsprays, or cosmetics, as these can damage the stone's surface.</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>Ultrasonic Cleaners</strong>
                                        <p>Never clean opals in ultrasonic jewelry cleaners, as the vibrations can cause cracking.</p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-md-6">
                                <ul class="avoid-list">
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>Direct Sunlight</strong>
                                        <p>Prolonged exposure to direct sunlight can cause opals to dry out and potentially crack.</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>Impact and Pressure</strong>
                                        <p>Opals are relatively soft and can be damaged by impacts. Remove opal jewelry before engaging in sports or physical activities.</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <strong>Oils and Grease</strong>
                                        <p>Natural oils from your skin can dull the appearance of opals over time. Clean your opal jewelry regularly to maintain its brilliance.</p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
                <div class="card h-100">
                    <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
                        <h3 class="mb-0">Professional Maintenance</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p>We recommend bringing your opal jewelry to Ottawa Opal Shop for professional cleaning and inspection once a year. Our experts will:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Thoroughly clean your jewelry using safe, professional methods</li>
                            <li>Check settings to ensure stones are secure</li>
                            <li>Inspect for any signs of damage or wear</li>
                            <li>Polish metal components to restore shine</li>
                            <li>Provide personalized advice for your specific pieces</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Professional maintenance helps extend the life of your opal jewelry and ensures it remains beautiful for years to come.</p>
                        <div class="text-center mt-3">
                            <a asp-area="" asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Contact" class="btn btn-primary">Schedule a Cleaning</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="col-md-6 mb-4">
                <div class="card h-100">
                    <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
                        <h3 class="mb-0">Opal Care Kit</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p>Ottawa Opal Shop offers a specialized Opal Care Kit that includes everything you need to maintain your opal jewelry at home:</p>
                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-md-6">
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Gentle opal cleaning solution</li>
                                    <li>Soft microfiber cleaning cloth</li>
                                    <li>Soft-bristled brush for settings</li>
                                    <li>Lined storage pouch</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-md-6">
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Humidity-controlled storage container</li>
                                    <li>Detailed care instructions</li>
                                    <li>Opal identification guide</li>
                                    <li>One-year warranty extension</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <p class="mt-3">Our care kit is designed specifically for opals and is safe for all types of opal jewelry. It makes a great addition to your collection or a thoughtful gift for opal jewelry owners.</p>
                        <div class="text-center mt-3">
                            <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Purchase Care Kit</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<style>
    .care-card {
        transition: transform 0.3s ease;
    }
    
    .care-card:hover {
        transform: translateY(-5px);
    }
    
    .care-icon {
        height: 80px;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
    }
    
    .avoid-list {
        list-style: none;
        padding-left: 0;
    }
    
    .avoid-list li {
        margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    
    .avoid-list li strong {
        color: #dc3545;
        display: block;
        margin-bottom: 5px;
        font-size: 1.1rem;
    }
    
    .avoid-list li p {
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }
</style>
